INSERT INTO `recipe_instructions` VALUES (25,444601,1,'In a 5-qt. slow cooker, combine peanuts. Layer with the remaining ingredients in order given (do not stir). Cover and cook on low for 2 to 2-1/2 hours or until chips are melted.'),(26,444601,2,'Stir to combine. Drop by tablespoonfuls onto waxed paper.'),(27,444601,3,'Let stand until set. Store in an airtight container at room temperature.'),(28,113524,1,'In a microwave-safe bowl, melt butter and chocolate; stir until smooth. Stir in the cracker crumbs, coconut, peanuts and wheat germ. Press into a greased 13x9-in. pan. Cover and refrigerate for at least 30 minutes.'),(29,113524,2,'In a small bowl, combine filling ingredients.'),(30,113524,3,'Spread over crust. Cover and refrigerate for at least 30 minutes.'),(31,113524,4,'In a microwave, melt chocolate and butter; stir until smooth.'),(32,113524,5,'Pour over filling. Cover and refrigerate for at least 30 minutes or until topping is set.'),(33,113524,6,'Cut into squares. Refrigerate leftovers.'),(34,228132,1,'Whizz the cauliflower up in a vitamix/food processor until fairly fine. Set it aside until you need it.'),(35,228132,2,'Saute the onion, garlic and ginger in the olive oil until the onion is soft and translucent.'),(36,228132,3,'Add the celery and carrots and saute gently until the carrots are tender'),(37,228132,4,'Next add the courgette and cook for another couple of minutes.'),(38,228132,5,'Spoon in the spices and mix well.'),(39,228132,6,'Pour in the cauliflower and mix until well coated in the spices.'),(40,228132,7,'Add the stock, cover and simmer gently for 15 - 20 minutes.'),(41,228132,8,'Add the peppers and sweetcorn and mix through.'),(42,228132,9,'Season with salt and pepper.1'),(43,228132,10,'Chop the tomatoes in quarters and add to the top of each dish as you serve it'),(44,577801,1,'Combine all ingredients in a shaker and shake until combined.'),(45,577801,2,'Serve over ice with a twist of lemon'),(46,50549,1,'For simple syrup: Put sugar and 2 tsp. water in a glass bowl and microwave on full power for 10 to 15 seconds, or until sugar is dissolved.'),(47,50549,2,'Drop blackberries, pineapple, and mint leaves into a sturdy glass and crush to a pulp with the end of a wooden spoon.'),(48,50549,3,'Add the simple syrup, lime juice, and rum.'),(49,50549,4,'Pour the contents into an old-fashioned glass and then back into first glass; repeat until thoroughly mixed, then pour back into old-fashioned glass.'),(50,50549,5,'Add ice cubes and seltzer; stir.'),(51,50549,6,'Garnish with sprig of mint and lime wedge.'),(52,494968,1,'Add the broth, linguine, onion, broccoli, asparagus, mushrooms, garlic, red pepper flakes, salt and pepper to a large pot set over high heat.'),(53,494968,2,'Drizzle the olive oil over the top.As soon as it comes to a boil, set the timer for 7 minutes and start tossing constantly with long-handled tongs. Continue boiling and tossing. As soon as the 7 minutes is up, add the peas, parsley, heavy whipping cream, Parmesan, and lemon zest and continue cooking, tossing constantly, for 1-2 more minutes, until the pasta and veggies appear tender.'),(54,494968,3,'Remove from heat. Note that much of the liquid will have evaporated, but not all. And that\'s okay!'),(55,494968,4,'Let the pasta sit for a couple of minutes to cool; the sauce will continue to thicken during that time. Taste and add additional salt and pepper if desired.'),(56,494968,5,'Garnish with additional Parmesan cheese.'),(57,779313,1,'Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F.'),(58,779313,2,'Combine pineapple, 2 tablespoons brown sugar and corn starch.'),(59,779313,3,'Place pineapple in an 8x8\" baking pan, or in individual baking dishes as pictured if desired.In a large bowl, combine butter,  cup brown sugar, oats and flour until combined. The texture will be that of a cookie dough -- easily pressed and held together. Crumble topping over the pineapple in baking dish and press down gently.'),(60,779313,4,'Bake for 45 minutes or until bubbly around the edges and golden brown on top.'),(61,779313,5,'Serve as desired with vanilla ice cream!'),(62,812124,1,'Place all ingredients in a blender and blend.'),(63,812124,2,'Pour and Enjoy'),(64,953869,1,'In a large bowl, combine flour, garlic, rosemary, salt, pepper and yeast.Using a wooden spoon or your hand, add water and mix until a wet, sticky dough forms, about 30 seconds.Cover bowl tightly with plastic wrap and let stand at room temperature until surface is dotted with bubbles, about 18 to 24 hours.Lightly oil a 10-inch cast iron skillet or coat with nonstick spray; sprinkle with cornmeal.Working on a lightly floured surface, gently shape dough into a round.'),(65,953869,2,'Place dough into the prepared skillet. Cover with a clean dishtowel and let stand at room temperature until dough has doubled in size and does not readily spring back when poked with a finger, about 2 hours.Preheat oven to 450 degrees F.'),(66,953869,3,'Place into oven and bake until golden brown, about 30-40 minutes.'),(67,953869,4,'Serve warm.'),(68,300106,1,'Put the garlic, anchovies, and capers in the work bowl of a food processor and pulse until finely chopped.'),(69,300106,2,'Add the arugula, cheese, lemon juice, and olive oil, and pulse until the mixture is completely combined and is the consistency of a classic pesto.'),(70,300106,3,'Add salt and pepper, to taste. To serve, spread on bread or crackers, or toss with pasta.'),(71,300106,4,'Transfer any remaining pesto to a freezer-safe airtight container and freeze for up to 1 month.'),(72,723984,1,'Place the shredded cabbage and scallions in a large bowl.'),(73,723984,2,'Heat a medium dry skillet over medium-low heat.'),(74,723984,3,'Add nuts and let toast, stirring every 20 seconds or so, until the nuts are lightly browning.'),(75,723984,4,'Add to cabbage mixture.In a small bowl, whisk together the ingredients for the dressing.'),(76,723984,5,'Pour over the cabbage and toss until everything is well combined and cabbage is coated. Taste and add more salt if desired.'),(77,723984,6,'Let sit for 5 minutes before serving.'),(78,1006419,1,'Make frosting: beat butter until creamy using a hand or a stand mixer. Slowly mix in powdered sugar, 1 cup at a time.'),(79,1006419,2,'Add salt and vanilla, then add 2 tablespoons of heavy whipping cream. Beat at medium high speed until smooth, adding more cream as needed for desired consistency.Divide the frosting into 3 bowls. Color each a different color: pink, blue, purple.Reynolds Kitchens Plastic Wrap Hack: lay out a piece of plastic wrap.'),(80,1006419,3,'Place one color frosting in the center and roll up like a log, squeezing the air out. Twist the ends to seal. Repeat with remaining colors of frosting.'),(81,1006419,4,'Cut of one tip of each plastic frosting log.'),(82,1006419,5,'Place all three, cut side first, into a large plastic pastry bag fitted with a 1M tip (or other desired tip).Prepare the cupcakes: cut a small hole in the center of the cupcake and remove the piece of cupcake. Fill the hole with sprinkles, then replace the bit of cupcake.Frost cupcakes with the swirl frosting. Top with additional sprinkles, if desired.Store in an airtight container in refrigerator for up to 4 days.'),(83,202880,1,'Ask a grown-up to prepare the grill.'),(84,487010,1,'Preheat grill for medium heat and lightly oil the grate.'),(85,487010,2,'Mix ground beef, green onion, hoisin sauce, Sriracha sauce, sesame oil, garlic powder, red pepper flakes, ginger, salt, and black pepper together in a bowl until thoroughly combined. Divide meat mixture into quarters; form each portion into a patty.Grill on the preheated grill until meat is browned and no longer pink inside, about 10 minutes per side.'),(86,201753,1,'1'),(87,201753,2,'Heat 1 teaspoon of vegetable oil in a 10- inch non stick skillet over medium high heat until shimmering.'),(88,201753,3,'Add chopped pancetta and cook, stirring until pancetta is crisp, about 5 minutes.'),(89,201753,4,'Add chopped shallots and cook, stirring frequently, until soft and translucent, about 5 minutes.'),(90,201753,5,'Transfer shallots and pancetta to a large bowl using a slotted spoon.'),(91,201753,6,'Transfer fat to a cup.'),(92,201753,7,'Add enough oil to add up to about 4 tablespoons total fate. Set skillet aside.'),(93,201753,8,'2'),(94,201753,9,'Using the largest holes on a box grater grate potatoes one at a time.'),(95,201753,10,'Place grated potato in the center of a clean tea towel and twist tea towel to drain out liquid over sink.'),(96,201753,11,'Transfer to bowl with pancetta and shallots. Season to taste with salt and pepper.'),(97,201753,12,'Add 1 1/2 teaspoons picked thyme leaves and toss to combine.'),(98,201753,13,'3'),(99,201753,14,'Wipe out skillet.'),(100,201753,15,'Heat 1 tablespoon of fat over medium heat, and when shimmering add 1/2 of potato mixture to the skillet. Using a rubber spatula, press into the bottom of the pan and cook until edges begin to look brown, about 6 minutes. Carefully slide roesti onto a plate then place another plate on top. Flip plates over, then slide roesti back into pan and continue to cook until completely crisp, about 7 minutes longer.'),(101,201753,16,'Transfer to a large plate and keep warm in a 200°F oven. Repeat with remaining fat and potato. Sprinkle roesti with thyme and serve with sour cream.'),(102,203677,1,'In a large skillet, heat the oil.'),(103,203677,2,'Add the sliced onion and a pinch of salt, cover and cook, stirring a few times, until the onion is crisp-tender and just turning translucent, 5 minutes. Stir in the hot sauce and beef broth and remove from the heat. Season with salt.'),(104,203677,3,'Heat a large griddle.'),(105,203677,4,'Spread the butter on 1 side of each bread slice and griddle buttered side down over moderate heat until toasted, about 2 minutes.'),(106,203677,5,'Transfer the toasts to a plate.'),(107,203677,6,'Add the bacon to the griddle and cook over moderate heat until crisp, about 4 minutes per side; drain on paper towels. Wipe off the griddle.'),(108,203677,7,'Season the beef patties with salt and cook on the griddle over moderately high heat until medium-rare, about 2 minutes per side. Top each burger with 1/4 cup of smoked Gouda and cook until the cheese melts, 1 minute.'),(109,203677,8,'Set the burgers on the unbuttered sides of 4 toasts. Top with the bacon, onion and Sweet Barbecue Sauce. Close the burgers and serve, passing more barbecue sauce at the table.'),(110,103321,1,'1'),(111,103321,2,'Combine cucumber, carrot, 1 teaspoon salt, sugar, and vinegar in a medium bowl and toss to combine. Set aside.'),(112,103321,3,'2'),(113,103321,4,'Divide meat into four even piles and shape into burger patties about 1/2-inch wider than burger buns. Season generously with salt and pepper and set aside.'),(114,103321,5,'3'),(115,103321,6,'Light one chimney full of charcoal. When all the charcoal is lit and covered with gray ash, pour out and spread the coals evenly over half of coal grate. Alternatively, set half the burners of a gas grill to high heat. Set cooking grate in place, cover gill and allow to preheat for 5 minutes. Clean and oil the grilling grate.'),(116,103321,7,'4'),(117,103321,8,'Place burgers directly over hot side of grill and cook until well charred, about 2 minutes. Flip patties and brush with sauce. Cook on second side until well charred, about 2 minutes longer, brushing with sauce occasionally. Flip burgers again, transfer to cooler side of grill, brush with more syrup, and continue to cook, brushing with sauce occasionally, until patty registers 125°F to 130°F on an instant read thermometer for medium rare, about 5 minutes total, or 135°F to 140°F for medium, about 6 minutes total. Top each burger patty with 1 slice cheese, then transfer to a large plate and tent with aluminum foil.'),(118,103321,9,'5'),(119,103321,10,'Toast buns directly over hot side of grill until browned, about 30 seconds.'),(120,103321,11,'6'),(121,103321,12,'Place bottom buns on a cutting board and top with burger patties. Top each burger with chopped kimchi, pickled carrots/cucumber, and scallions.'),(122,103321,13,'Drizzle with more sauce. Close sandwiches and serve.'),(126,491574,1,'Pour 1 cup of water in a small saucepan.'),(127,491574,2,'Add tea bags & bring to a boil. Just as water comes to a boil, remove from heat & cover to steep.  Allow to steep for 5 minutes.'),(128,491574,3,'Pour tea into pitcher with sugar.'),(129,491574,4,'Add remaining water & stir well to combine & melt sugar.  Allow tea to cool in refrigerator for 1 hour.'),(130,491574,5,'Add peach nectar to tea & stir well to combine.'),(131,631759,1,'In a medium bowl combine the dry ingredients.'),(132,631759,2,'Make a well in the center and pour the olive oil and lukewarm water into the well.'),(133,631759,3,'Knead the dough with your hands for 5-10 minutes.'),(134,631759,4,'Divide the dough into 16 equal pieces.'),(135,631759,5,'Take two pieces and stretch the dough into thin strips (about 30-35 cm long).'),(136,631759,6,'Cover the rest of the dough to prevent it from drying out.'),(137,631759,7,'Place 2 strips side-by-side, pinch the ends. Twist them together and pinch to join the ends.'),(138,631759,8,'Place the rings on baking sheets lined with parchment paper.'),(139,631759,9,'Let the dough sit in a warm place for 20-30 minutes.1'),(140,631759,10,'Preheat the oven to 200C.1'),(141,631759,11,'Pour the sesame seeds into the pan and turn the fire on medium heat.1'),(142,631759,12,'Stir the seeds every 4-5 minutes until golden. Set aside.1'),(143,631759,13,'Pour molasses and boiling water into a bowl big enough to fit your rings.1'),(144,631759,14,'Whisk to dissolve the molasses completely.1'),(145,631759,15,'Put the sesame seeds in another bowl.1'),(146,631759,16,'Dip both sides of the rings in the liquid, drain excess moisture, then coat both sides in the sesame seeds.1'),(147,631759,17,'Transfer them to the baking sheets.1'),(148,631759,18,'Bake in preheated oven for about 17 minutes.'),(149,600763,1,'Wash moong dal under running cold water till water runs clear.Take moong dal with 1 cup of water in pressure cooker. Close the lid, put the weight on and cook it for 2 whistles on medium heat.'),(150,600763,2,'Let the pressure go down by itself, open the cover and it will look like this.'),(151,600763,3,'Heat the oil in pan on medium heat. Once hot add mustard seeds, let them pop. Then add cumin seeds and let them sizzle.'),(152,600763,4,'Add ginger paste and green chilies. Cook for 30 seconds.'),(153,600763,5,'Add curry leaves and sauté for 30 seconds again.'),(154,600763,6,'Add chopped onion and mix.'),(155,600763,7,'Add salt to make the cooking process faster.'),(156,600763,8,'Let them cook till light brown.'),(157,600763,9,'Add turmeric powder, red chili powder and coriander powder.'),(158,600763,10,'Mix well. And cook for a minutes.'),(159,600763,11,'Add cooked dal and another 1 ½ cups of water. Adjust the water quantity as per your liking.'),(160,600763,12,'Mix well.'),(161,600763,13,'Let it come to a boil and let it simmer for 5 minutes.Moong dal fry is ready to serve.'),(162,366101,1,'In a blender or food processor, blend apricots and liquid until smooth.'),(163,366101,2,'Pour into a large saucepan.'),(164,366101,3,'Add pineapple juice, cider and orange juice.'),(165,366101,4,'Place the cloves and cinnamon sticks in a double thickness of cheesecloth; bring up corners of cloth and tie with a string to form a bag.'),(166,366101,5,'Add to saucepan. (Or place loose spices in saucepan and strain before serving.) Bring to a boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer 15-20 minutes.'),(167,366101,6,'Serve hot in mugs.'),(168,366101,7,'Garnish with cinnamon sticks if desired.'),(169,487665,1,'In a deep mixing bowl (glass or metal works best), whisk together the instant whipped topping and instant pudding mix.'),(170,487665,2,'Add milk and beat on low speed until blended.Increase mix speed to high and beat for 4 to 6 minutes, until stiff peaks form.Frost cakes, cheesecakes, cupcakes, or just go to town with a spoon!'),(171,559187,1,'Preheat oven to 375 F degrees.'),(172,559187,2,'Roll out the puff pastry a bit, so that it\'s about 18 inches x 14 inches. You\'ll need about 4 inches down the center of the pastry, so start cutting 1 inch strips, leaving the 4 inches in the center.'),(173,559187,3,'Add a tablespoon of butter to a skillet and melt it.'),(174,559187,4,'Add the mushrooms and kielbasa and fry for a couple minutes. In the meantime, whisk together 6 eggs and mix with the shredded Swiss cheese.'),(175,559187,5,'Add the eggs to the skillet and cook.'),(176,559187,6,'Add the parsley for color and season with salt and pepper.'),(177,559187,7,'Let the scrambled eggs cool.'),(178,559187,8,'Place the scrambled eggs in the center of the pastry.Take a strip from each side and fold over the eggs. One from each side at a time, sort of forming this braid.'),(179,559187,9,'Brush the pastry with the egg wash and bake in the oven for about half hour or until nice and golden brown.'),(180,445187,1,'In a large bowl, combine the spinach, broccoli, carrots, water chestnuts and sunflower kernels. In a blender or food processor, combine the dressing ingredients; cover and process until smooth.'),(181,445187,2,'Serve with salad.'),(182,582938,1,'Wash the rice with cold water until the water runs clear.'),(183,582938,2,'Drain well. If you have a rice maker (way easier!), follow rice maker instructions and cook on the white rice setting then skip to step #4Put drained rice in a heavy sauce-pan and add 2 cups cold water. Cover tightly and set the pan over high heat and bring to a boil. Once it boils, reduce heat to medium and let cook covered until all the water is absorbed (7-8 min). Do not remove the cover to check, but listen for the bubbling to stop.Once you hear a faint hissing sound, reduce the heat to very low and cook another 6 min.'),(184,582938,3,'Remove from the heat and let stand 15 min covered. This is the basic white rice eaten with japanese meals.'),(185,582938,4,'Transfer the hot rice to a large bowl and break it up to get rid of all the hot clumps.'),(186,582938,5,'Let the rice cool down until it is just warm, then stir in your cooled sushi vinegar'),(187,582938,6,'Wrap your sushi matt in plastic wrap before using it (this makes it re-useable and you don\'t even have to wash it!).Fold the pieces of nori in half to split them.Toast your sesame seeds over medium heat, stirring constantly until golden. Slice up your veggies.'),(188,582938,7,'Spread a generous handful of sushi rice onto the ½ sheet of nori. Use your WET FINGER TIPS (keep your hands wet to prevent sticking) to spread the rice evenly over the entire surface of the nori.Flip the rice covered piece of nori over so the rice is facing down (this way, your rice will be on the outside).'),(189,582938,8,'Place your fillings across the center of your rice in the middle of the sheet (don\'t overfill or the roll won\'t seal).Start rolling away from you using your matt to firmly keep the roll in place. Apply some pressure to make a tight roll. If its not tight enough, it will be difficult to cut. Once the roll is complete, sprinkle the roll with toasted sesame seeds while it is still on the mat so you can turn it easily.Run your sharp knife through a damp paper towel before slicing so the rice won\'t stick as much.'),(190,582938,9,'Cut the roll in half, then line the two halves up and slice even 1-inch rings. I have found that it slices easier when you slice quickly.'),(191,205186,1,'1'),(192,205186,2,'In a small saucepan heat 1 1/2 cups of Coca Cola over medium high heat until it reduces to just 1/2 a cup of cola concentrate, about 15 minutes.'),(193,205186,3,'Remove from heat and set aside to cool. While coke is reducing, whip cream and granulated sugar in a stand mixer or by hand until stiff peaks are formed.'),(194,205186,4,'Combine confectioner\'s sugar and cinnamon in a large bowl and set aside.'),(195,205186,5,'2'),(196,205186,6,'Heat oil to 360°F in a large Dutch oven and adjust flame to maintain temperature. While oil is heating prepare the fritter batter.'),(197,205186,7,'3'),(198,205186,8,'In a large bowl whisk together remaining 1/3 cup of Coca Cola with vanilla. Stir in Bisquick to form a sticky dough. Sprinkle surface of dough with flour until a pliant and less sticky dough forms. Turn the dough out onto a generously floured surface. Flatten the dough into a large square about 1/2\' thick and cut into 3/4\' square pieces.'),(199,205186,9,'Roll each square into a little ball.'),(200,205186,10,'4'),(201,205186,11,'One at a time, place the balls in a shallow heat-resistant strainer then carefully transfer to the hot oil, cooking no more than 4 at a time. Fry for 1 to 2 minutes or until golden on the bottom. Then using heat resistant strainer or tongs, carefully turn fritters and fry until golden brown on second side, about 1 minute longer. Use strainer to remove fritters from hot oil.'),(202,205186,12,'Transfer to a paper towel lined wire cooling rack. Repeat, cooking in batches, until all the dough balls have been fried.'),(203,205186,13,'5'),(204,205186,14,'Toss fritters in cinnamon sugar. Divide the fritters among four low ball glasses, drizzle fritters with Coke concentrate then top with whipped cream and a cherry.'),(205,205186,15,'Serve immediately.'),(206,28940,1,'Preheat oven to 275 degrees. Throw chuck roasts into a large, heavy pot.'),(207,28940,2,'Pour on the roasted red peppers, the drained artichoke hearts, and the sun dried tomatoes. If the sun dried tomatoes are packed in oil, drizzle in about a tablespoon of the oil.'),(208,28940,3,'Add onions, garlic cloves and beef broth, then place the lid on the pot and cook in the oven for four hours.'),(209,28940,4,'Remove the pot after four hours and use a fork to confirm that the meat is falling apart/fork tender. (If not, put back into the oven for 30 minute increments until totally tender.)With a slotted spoon, remove the peppers, artichokes, onions, garlic, and sundried tomatoes and place them in a separate container.'),(210,28940,5,'Remove the meat and place it in another separate containers. Cover the containers holding the veggies and meat and refrigerate them several hours or overnight.'),(211,28940,6,'Place the lid on the pot and refrigerate it for several hours or overnight. When you\'re ready to serve the roast, remove the meat and veggie bowls from the fridge and nuke them just to heat them up. Set aside. Cook egg noodles according to package directions.'),(212,28940,7,'Drain and set aside.'),(213,28940,8,'Remove the pot from the fridge and carefully skim off the solidified fat from the top of the liquid. Discard the fat.'),(214,28940,9,'Mix flour with 1/2 cup of the cooking liquid and set aside.'),(215,28940,10,'Add wine to the cooking liquid then bring it to a boil over high heat. Boil the liquid for several minutes, until it reduces by at least half. When bubbles appear all over the surface of the liquid, drizzle in a tablespoon or so of the flour paste. Check thickness: if it\'s too liquidy, continue to boil for another minute or two. If it\'s too thick, add some more broth or water. You want to wind up with a rich, thick liquid/gravy.Arrange cooked noodles on a large platter and arrange chunks of the meat and the intact artichoke hearts and peppers (and garlic cloves!) all around the meat. Spoon the thick gravy all over the top and sprinkle on minced fresh parsley.'),(216,28940,11,'Serve immediately! Very, very flavorful.'),(217,715328,1,'Peel, core and slice the apples.Toss all of the apples with  cup of the sugar.'),(218,715328,2,'Pour the apples in a colander set over a large bowl and allow to drain for 1 hours.While the apples are setting prepare your pie dough and let it set in the fridge for a hour.Adjust an oven rack to the lowest position and place a rimmed baking sheet on the rack.'),(219,715328,3,'Heat the oven to 500 degrees.In a large bowl, toss the apples with the remainder of sugar, brown sugar, flour, lemon juice, sea salt, nutmeg, and cinnamon. Set mixture aside.'),(220,715328,4,'Roll out the double pie crust on a floured surface then place the bottom crust in the pie pan.'),(221,715328,5,'Pour the apple mixture into the pie crust, than top with the top pie crust. Crimp the edges of the crust using your fingers.'),(222,715328,6,'Cut 4-5 vent holes in the top of the pie crust.'),(223,715328,7,'Brush the top crust with the beaten egg white, and then sprinkle the sugar in the raw on top.'),(224,715328,8,'Place the pie on the hot baking sheet in the oven then reduce the temperature to 425 degrees.'),(225,715328,9,'Bake until the top crust is golden brown, this should take 20-25 minutes.Once the top is golden brown, rotate the baking sheet, and turn the temperature down to 375 degrees.'),(226,715328,10,'Bake another 30-35 minutes, until the top crust is a deep golden brown.'),(227,715328,11,'Remove the pie from the oven and allow it to cool before serving.Top with a big scoop of vanilla ice cream for an extra treat.'),(230,594589,1,'In a medium bowl, whisk together all the ingredients for the dressing.Toss kale leaves and your desired amount of dressing together.Store dressing in a jar in the refrigerator for up to 3 months.'),(231,582031,1,'Mix flour, instant yeast, sugar and salt.'),(232,582031,2,'Pour olive oil and add water little by little. Use your hand to combine them well until you have a soft dough.Cover it and wait to rise for an hour.'),(233,582031,3,'Heat olive oil in a skillet.'),(234,582031,4,'Add ground beef and onion, cover it so that it releases its water.When it starts to absorb its water, add peppers and spices, stir.Cook it for about 10 minutes stirring occasionally.'),(235,582031,5,'Let it cool.'),(236,582031,6,'Add chopped parsley when it cools.Preheat oven at 180C.Dust a little flour on the counter or on a wooden board. Make a log from dough and cut it into 16-18 eaqual balls.Dust the counter again and roll one of the balls out thin giving it an oval shape.'),(237,582031,7,'Place baking paper in an oven tray and put this oval shaped thin dough on it.Put some filling in it and stick the edges of pide.Repeat the same steps until you finish all balls.'),(238,582031,8,'Brush each pide with olive oil and bake them at 180C until golden, for about 20 minutes.'),(240,191852,1,'Melt 1 1/2 tablespoons butter in a small heavy saucepan over moderate heat and whisk in flour, then cook roux, whisking constantly, 2 minutes.'),(241,191852,2,'Add broth in a slow stream, whisking constantly, and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer, whisking occasionally, 3 minutes.'),(242,191852,3,'Remove from heat and keep warm.'),(243,191852,4,'Pat beef dry and season well with salt and pepper.'),(244,191852,5,'Heat 1 tablespoon butter with 1 tablespoon oil in a 12-inch heavy skillet over moderately high heat until foam subsides. Sauté beef in two batches, turning once, until browned on both sides but still pink inside, about 1 minute.'),(245,191852,6,'Transfer to a plate with a slotted spoon.'),(246,191852,7,'Heat remaining tablespoon butter with remaining tablespoon oil in same skillet over moderately high heat until hot but not smoking, then sauté shallot, stirring occasionally, until golden brown, about 3 minutes.'),(247,191852,8,'Add mushrooms and sauté, stirring occasionally, until liquid mushrooms give off is evaporated and mushrooms are browned, about 8 to 10 minutes. Return meat with its juices to skillet and stir to combine, then transfer to a platter.'),(248,191852,9,'Reheat sauce over low heat (do not let boil), then whisk in sour cream, mustard, dill, salt, and pepper.'),(249,191852,10,'Pour sauce over beef and serve immediately.'),(250,615454,1,'Place cashews in a bowl and add enough water to cover. Soak the cashews overnight, or for 8 hours. For a quick-soak method, soak the cashews in boiled water for 30 to 60 minutes.'),(251,615454,2,'Drain and rinse the cashews.In a blender, combine the soaked and drained cashews with 1 cup of vegetable broth and blend on the highest speed until smooth. Set aside.In a large pot, heat the oil over medium heat.'),(252,615454,3,'Add the garlic and onion and saut for 3 to 5 minutes, or until the onion is translucent. Season generously with Herbamare or sea salt.'),(253,615454,4,'Add the carrots, bell pepper, potato, celery, and diced tomatoes with their juices, the remaining 5 cups broth, and 10-Spice'),(254,615454,5,'Mix. Stir well to combine . Bring the mixture to a boil and then reduce the heat to medium-low. Season with salt and black pepper.Simmer the soup uncovered for at least 20 minutes, stirring occasionally, until the vegetables are tender. Season with salt and black pepper. During the last 5 minutes of cooking, stir in the cashew cream, spinach (or kale), and drained beans.'),(255,615454,6,'Add more 10-Spice'),(256,615454,7,'Mix, to taste.To freeze, ladle the soup into containers (leaving 1 inch for expansion), cool completely, secure lid, and place in the freezer for up to 6 weeks.'),(258,595093,1,'Preheat oven to 450 degrees.'),(259,595093,2,'Place peeled potatoes in a large pot and cover with salted water. Bring to a boil and then reduce to a simmer. Cook until potatoes are soft enough to mash - easily pierced with a knife or fork (15 to 20 minutes).While potatoes are cooking, heat oil in a heavy bottomed 6 quart pot over medium-high heat.'),(260,595093,3,'Add carrots, celery, onion, garlic, thyme and oregano. Cook, stirring occasionally, until vegetables are tender (approximately 10 minutes).'),(261,595093,4,'Add ground beef and stir into vegetables. Cook mixture until beef is no longer pink.'),(262,595093,5,'Add 1 cup water and bring to a boil, simmering for 1 minute.'),(263,595093,6,'Add flour, tomato paste, hot sauce, browning and seasoning sauce, Worcestershire sauce, and salt and pepper (adjusting to your taste) and cook, blending well for about a 1 minute.'),(264,595093,7,'Remove from heat.'),(265,595093,8,'Drain potatoes well and return to the pot. Mash the potatoes and then add milk and all but  cup of cheddar cheese, stirring to mix well so the cheddar begins to melt. Stir until smooth, adding additional milk if necessary. Season cheddar-potato topping with salt and pepper to your liking.'),(266,595093,9,'Pour beef filling into a 13-by-9-inch ungreased baking dish. Drop dollops of the potato mixture over the beef filling and spread the potatoes to the edges of the dish with a spatula.Using a fork, make decorative peaks in the mashed potatoes, and then sprinkle with the remaining  cup of grated cheese.'),(267,595093,10,'Place a sheet of aluminum foil on the center rack of your oven to prevent any oven spills, and then place the baking dish on the foil in the oven.'),(268,595093,11,'Bake at 450 degrees until topping is browned and filling is bubbling rapidly, about 25-30 minutes.'),(269,595093,12,'Let stand 5 minutes or longer to set up before serving.'),(270,598130,1,'Preheat oven to 450ºF.'),(271,598130,2,'Place the Oreos in a gallon sized ziptop bag. Press all the air out of the bag and seal it well. Use a rolling pin to crush the cookies until all large chunks are gone. Open the bag and pour in the melted butter. Seal the bag and \"smush\" the butter and the Oreos together until well incorporated.Press the Oreo crumbs into a 9-inch pie dish. It\'s ok if the crust doesn\'t come all the way up the sides.'),(272,598130,3,'Whisk together all of the pumpkin pie filling ingredients until smooth, and pour into the prepared pie crust.'),(273,598130,4,'Bake at 450º for 10 minutes, and then reduce the heat to 400º and bake for another 30 minutes. Turn off the oven and crack the oven door, and let the pie cool in the oven. Chill until serving.'),(274,871974,1,'Preheat oven to 42'),(275,871974,2,'Place carrots in the center of a large square of foil and drizzle with 2 Tbsp. water. Wrap foil around carrots to make a tightly sealed packet.'),(276,871974,3,'Place on a foil-lined rimmed baking sheet and roast until carrots are very tender, 4050 minutes.'),(277,871974,4,'Let sit until cool enough to handle.Process roasted carrots, chickpeas, tahini, lemon juice, garlic, harissa, salt, and cumin in a food processor until mixture is smooth, about 1 minute. With the motor running, stream in 2 Tbsp. oil, then continue to process until hummus is very light and creamy, about 1 minute longer. Taste and season with salt, if needed.'),(278,871974,5,'Add more harissa to make hummus spicier, if desired, then process to incorporate, just a few seconds longer.'),(279,871974,6,'Transfer hummus to a shallow bowl. Top with sunflower seeds and parsley and drizzle with oil.Do Ahead: Hummus can be made 4 days ahead.'),(280,871974,7,'Transfer to an airtight container and chill.'),(281,249107,1,'Cook the bacon in a large sauce pan until crispy, set aside on paper towels to drain and pour off the excess grease.'),(282,249107,2,'Heat the oil in the pan over medium heat, add onion and jalapeno peppers and cook until tender, about 5-7 minutes.'),(283,249107,3,'Add the garlic and cook until fragrant, about a minute.'),(284,249107,4,'Add the broth, bacon, chicken and beans and simmer for 15 minutes, seasoning with salt and pepper to taste.'),(285,249107,5,'Add the corn, cream cheese and cheddar cheese and stir it in until the cheeses melt.'),(286,235325,1,'Top the pizza dough with marinara, sausage, and mozzarella cheese.'),(287,235325,2,'Bake at 450 for 15 minutes or until the crust is browned. Top the pizza with basil leaves.'),(288,506312,1,'Mix the olive oil, mustard, honey and vinegar in a small bowl to make the dressing.'),(289,506312,2,'Add all remaining ingredients to a large bowl and top with the dressing.Toss everything together making sure to coat all the kale with the dressing. I used tongs and just kept tossing until all the leaves looked wet.Pile on a plate and dig in..I’ve made it 2 days in a row now!');
